A ministerial meeting of Africa's lumber producers is set to take place in Cabinda, Angola, with specialists preparing at a specially built center.
The meeting will focus on new policies for lumber imports and exports, as well as the protection of tropical rain forests.
The African Timber Organization, consisting of 13 member states, will convene in Angola for the 17th Africa Timber Conference.
Discussions will revolve around timber industry development and conservation efforts.
In another part of the world, China is taking urgent steps to protect black gibbons in Hainan province, emphasizing environmental preservation and sustainable practices.
